cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving the performance of acoustic models for speech recognition using deep Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes papers on natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also discusses techniques for improving the accuracy and speed of the models, which could fall under the categories of cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
